# ferox-isaac-demo DDS configuration — both vars optional.
#
# This file is sourced by scripts/lib/env.sh (which all demo scripts source),
# so the values flow to BOTH:
#   - the Isaac Sim container (mounted cyclone XML + CYCLONEDDS_URI -e flag)
#   - the Ferox nav stack (compose passthrough via docker/.env on the Ferox side)
#
# Set both when running cross-machine over a tunnel/VPN/router that drops
# multicast (Tailscale, WireGuard, some venue networks).
#
# Dev (single Vast.ai box, sim + nav co-located, mic over Tailscale from host):
#   FEROX_DDS_INTERFACE=tailscale0
#   FEROX_DDS_PEERS="100.82.193.45 100.120.68.65"
#
# Single-machine sim (sim, nav, speech all on same machine, no Tailscale):
#   leave both unset/commented — multicast on the local loopback/LAN.
